three and a half day festival

00:15:03.550 --> 00:15:06.160
in the dunes west of Timbuktu.

00:15:06.160 --> 00:15:10.020
I mean, it was an amazing
time in this desolate place

00:15:10.020 --> 00:15:13.470
that I had visited
1995, completely cut off

00:15:13.470 --> 00:15:16.120
from the world, transformed
in the course of less

00:15:16.120 --> 00:15:18.010
than a decade into
this happening

00:15:18.010 --> 00:15:20.210
town on the edge of the Sahara.

00:15:20.210 --> 00:15:25.780
2011, the Arab Spring happened,
including the downfall

00:15:25.780 --> 00:15:27.210
of Muammar Qaddafi.

00:15:27.210 --> 00:15:28.940
In the years before
that, you had

00:15:28.940 --> 00:15:33.900
this Islamic, Islamist movement
percolating in the Sahara

00:15:33.900 --> 00:15:37.570
as Islamist movements tend
to do in parts of the world

00:15:37.570 --> 00:15:40.212
where there is poor government,
where there's a lot of poverty,

00:15:40.212 --> 00:15:41.920
where there's very
little infrastructure,

00:15:41.920 --> 00:15:44.340
very little security.

00:15:44.340 --> 00:15:46.480
Islamist extremists
love a vacuum.

00:15:46.480 --> 00:15:49.220
And that's what the Sahara
and the area around Timbuktu

00:15:49.220 --> 00:15:50.520
offered.

00:15:50.520 --> 00:15:52.380
So in addition to
the fact that you

00:15:52.380 --> 00:15:55.150
