00:16:27.610 --> 00:16:30.480
let's call it, and 2011.

00:16:30.480 --> 00:16:35.670
That, in turn, allowed them to
buy weapons to recruit fighters

00:16:35.670 --> 00:16:38.860
from across North Africa
and the Middle East.

00:16:38.860 --> 00:16:41.060
All this was going
on simultaneous

00:16:41.060 --> 00:16:45.140
with this cultural
flowering in the desert.

00:16:45.140 --> 00:16:48.580
So you had these two
different dynamics

00:16:48.580 --> 00:16:51.220
happening simultaneously.

00:16:51.220 --> 00:16:54.470
What changed the whole
dynamic completely was 2011,

00:16:54.470 --> 00:16:55.380
was the Arab Spring.

00:16:55.380 --> 00:16:58.850
Getting back to that--
Qaddafi's regime fell.

00:16:58.850 --> 00:17:01.450
You may remember in
the-- Qaddafi was killed,

00:17:01.450 --> 00:17:04.119
I think, in July
or August, 2011.

00:17:04.119 --> 00:17:07.274
The armories were
opened-- chaos.

00:17:07.274 --> 00:17:09.690
NATO had been in there and
bombed the hell out of Qaddafi,

00:17:09.690 --> 00:17:12.579
but nobody kind of thought about
what the consequences would be.

00:17:12.579 --> 00:17:15.869
I think Obama said recently that
his biggest regret as president

00:17:15.869 --> 00:17:19.420
