00:18:24.910 --> 00:18:30.410
and making life
extremely difficult

00:18:30.410 --> 00:18:34.400
for the residents of Timbuktu
and across the north.

00:18:34.400 --> 00:18:38.540
At this point, this is when
the final act of my story

00:18:38.540 --> 00:18:43.810
unfolds, which is the
incredibly elaborate though

00:18:43.810 --> 00:18:47.720
low-tech smuggling operation
that Abdel Kader Haidara then

00:18:47.720 --> 00:18:51.140
engaged in, because he
believed that at some point--

00:18:51.140 --> 00:18:54.420
although they had not
specifically threatened

00:18:54.420 --> 00:18:57.520
to destroy these
manuscripts, he was

00:18:57.520 --> 00:19:00.190
all but certain that the
jihadists at some point

00:19:00.190 --> 00:19:01.420
would target them.

00:19:01.420 --> 00:19:03.970
Because he saw what
they stood for, as well

00:19:03.970 --> 00:19:07.470
many other people saw, as
anathema, as heretical,

00:19:07.470 --> 00:19:11.100
as antithetical to everything
that is in accordance

00:19:11.100 --> 00:19:12.940
with Wahabbist philosophy.

00:19:12.940 --> 00:19:16.810
So Abdel Kader then embarked
upon this incredibly elaborate

00:19:16.810 --> 00:19:20.640
effort using a network of
smugglers, volunteers, fellow

00:19:20.640 --> 00:19:22.990
bad-ass librarians,
relatives, et

00:19:22.990 --> 00:19:31.300
cetera to smuggle these by road,
by boat along the Niger River

00:19:31.300 --> 00:19:33.120
to the safety of Bamako.

00:19:33.120 --> 00:19:37.680
The last stages of this
period were in early 2013

00:19:37.680 --> 00:19:40.070
